PrecisEnactment of REGULATIONS AMENDING CERTAIN REGULATIONS MADE UNDER THE FISHERIES ACT (MISCELLANEOUS PROGRAM) which exempt fishing and related activities carried out under the authority of an Aboriginal Communal Fishing Licence from the application of specific provisions of the Regulations set out below, and authorize the Minister or an aboriginal organization to designate the persons who and the vessels that may be used to fish under the authority of such a licence. . 1. Northwest Territories Fishery Regulations 2. Yukon Territory Fishery Regulations 3. Newfoundland Fishery Regulations 4. Atlantic Fishery Regulations, 1985 5. Ontario Fishery Regulations, 1989 6. Quebec Fishery Regulations, 1990 7. Fishery (General) Regulations 8. Pacific Fishery Regulations, 1993 9. Maritime Provinces Fishery Regulations 10. Aboriginal Communal Fishing Licences Regulations 11. British Columbia Sport Fishing Regulations, 1996 .
